---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Programs" description="Scholarship eligibility, selection criteria, and program details for Resolute Ambitions.">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow dark">Programs</div>
      <h1>Scholarships, transparently awarded.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Resolute Ambitions awards merit-based scholarships to two eligible groups. Funds cover educational expenses paid directly to accredited institutions on the recipient's behalf.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Who we serve</h2>
      <p>Our charitable class consists of:</p>
      <ul class="checked">
        <li>U.S. citizens or permanent residents.</li>
        <li>High school juniors or seniors enrolled in or accepted to accredited colleges or universities with ROTC programs, <em>or</em></li>
        <li>Active-duty enlisted members of any U.S. military branch pursuing undergraduate education for officer commissioning.</li>
        <li>Individuals demonstrating genuine intent to pursue a military officer career.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What scholarships cover</h2>
      <ul class="checked">
        <li>Tuition and mandatory fees</li>
        <li>Room and board</li>
        <li>Books and required educational materials</li>
        <li>Educational testing and certification fees (e.g., standardized tests)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How recipients are selected</h2>
      <p>
        Scholarships are awarded through a competitive, merit-based selection process. An independent selection committee — composed of board members and community volunteers with relevant expertise (educators, military veterans, financial professionals) — reviews all applications. No committee member may participate in decisions involving applicants with whom they have a personal relationship.
      </p>
      <p>The committee evaluates:</p>
      <ul class="checked">
        <li>Academic achievement and potential</li>
        <li>Demonstrated commitment to military service</li>
        <li>Financial need</li>
        <li>Leadership qualities and extracurricular involvement</li>
        <li>Letters of recommendation</li>
        <li>A personal statement describing military service goals</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disbursement</h2>
      <p>
        Funds are paid directly to accredited educational institutions on behalf of recipients — never to individuals — to ensure funds are used exclusively for educational purposes. Enrollment status and satisfactory academic progress are verified before each disbursement.
      </p>

      <h2>Ongoing commitment</h2>
      <p>Recipients must:</p>
      <ul class="checked">
        <li>Maintain satisfactory academic progress</li>
        <li>Remain enrolled in ROTC or maintain intent to pursue officer commissioning</li>
        <li>Provide annual progress reports</li>
        <li>Notify the organization of any changes in educational or military service plans</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Educational outreach</h2>
      <p>
        Beyond direct scholarships, Resolute Ambitions provides information about military officer career pathways, offers guidance on scholarship and commissioning program applications, and hosts informational workshops for prospective applicants.
      </p>

      <div class="callout" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        Applications are not yet open. We will publish the application form and timeline here once 501(c)(3) status is granted and the inaugural scholarship cycle is funded. <a href="/contact">Reach out</a> if you want to be notified.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
